 ; along with GCC; see the file COPYING3.  If not see
 ; <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.
 
+mexpand-asm
+Target Report Mask(EXPAND_ASM)
+Expand certain inline assembly into rtl patterns that the compiler can
+better optimize.
+mbme
+Target Report RejectNegative
+Compile using the BME headers and libraries
+
+mnewlib
+Target Report RejectNegative
+Compile using the newlib headers and libraries
 m32
 Target Report RejectNegative
 Compile with 32 bit longs and pointers, which is the only supported
@@ -34,3 +45,20 @@ Known TILEPro CPUs (for use with the -mc
 EnumValue
 Enum(tilepro_cpu) String(tilepro) Value(0)
 
+Wunmatched-loop-pragmas
+Target Report Mask(WARN_UNMATCHED_LOOP_PRAGMAS)
+Warn about loop pragmas that do not have matching loops.
+;; The following are x86 options that are here for x86 compatibility.
+;; We simply ignore them.
+
+march=
+Target RejectNegative Joined Var(tilepro_arch_string)
+Ignored (x86 compatibility flag)
+
+momit-leaf-frame-pointer
+Target Report
+Ignored (x86 compatibility flag)
+
+mtune=
+Target RejectNegative Joined Var(tilepro_tune_string)
+Ignored (x86 compatibility flag)
diff -r -u -p -N /home/packages/gcc-4.8.2/gcc/config/tilepro/tilepro2.c ./gcc/config/tilepro/tilepro2.c
--- /home/packages/gcc-4.8.2/gcc/config/tilepro/tilepro2.c	1969-12-31 19:00:00.000000000 -0500
+++ ./gcc/config/tilepro/tilepro2.c	2015-10-26 22:26:34.339996000 -0400
@@ -0,0 +1,1712 @@
+/* Subroutines used for code generation on the Tilera TILEPro.
+   Copyright (C) 2011
+   Free Software Foundation, Inc.
+   Contributed by Walter Lee (walt@tilera.com)
+
+   This file is part of GCC.
+
+   GCC is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify it
+   under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published
+   by the Free Software Foundation; either version 3, or (at your
